  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "As of now the downward API for resource specification defaults to `0` for `limits` when `limits` are not specified in the pod spec. This behavior is not ideal for applications. \nWhat does a limit of `0` mean? \nIn reality, not having a limit translates to being limited by node capacity as of now, and node allocatable in the future once it is enforced. \nWe should default to node capacity instead of setting `limit.memory` to `0` when `limits` are not set.\nAnd for `limits.cpu` we should again default to node capacity and allocatable in the future.\n",
